OL,7,FCroucher convinced an elderly man with
OL,8,Fdementia to pay him more than #6,000
OL,9,Ffor items for his garden, which never
OL,10,Fmaterialised. The fraudster also stole
OL,11,Fthree iPhones from him.
OL,13,FSeparately, Croucher charged an
OL,14,Felderly woman who had recently been
OL,15,Fwidowed #2,240 to clear her garden -
OL,16,Falmost three times the amount he had
OL,17,Foriginally quoted her. The money also
OL,18,Fincluded payments for skips that he
OL,19,Fnever actually ordered or used.
